Company Overview of KP Building Products Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
KP Building Products Inc. manufactures building materials. Its manufacturing processes and products include ChromaLock process, which fuses the molecular structure of acrylic and vinyl to keep colors from fading; Cyclone System nail hem that provides extra rigidity and wind resistance; Ultra-Vinyl, a UV technology that combines vinyl compounds and UV inhibitors to combat the harsh rays of the sun; and Insta-Lock system that promotes a tighter panel lock. The company also offers vinyl sidings and accessories, shingles, soffits and decorative trim systems, and aluminum sidings. In addition, it offers accents, including aluminum soffits, fascia, trims, and rainware. The company serves architect...
KP Building Products Inc. manufactures building materials. Its manufacturing processes and products include ChromaLock process, which fuses the molecular structure of acrylic and vinyl to keep colors from fading; Cyclone System nail hem that provides extra rigidity and wind resistance; Ultra-Vinyl, a UV technology that combines vinyl compounds and UV inhibitors to combat the harsh rays of the sun; and Insta-Lock system that promotes a tighter panel lock. The company also offers vinyl sidings and accessories, shingles, soffits and decorative trim systems, and aluminum sidings. In addition, it offers accents, including aluminum soffits, fascia, trims, and rainware. The company serves architects, contractors, and homeowners in North America and internationally. KP Building Products Inc. was formerly known as LP Building Products, Inc. The company was incorporated in 2005 and is based in Holly Springs, Mississippi. KP Building Products Inc. operates as a subsidiary of Kaycan Limited.
